
[1]abjure

   ABJU'RE, v.t. [L. abjuro, to deny upon oath, from ab and juro, to
   swear.]

   1. To renounce upon oath; to abandon; as to abjure allegiance to a
   prince.

   2. To renounce or reject with solemnity; to reject; as to abjure
   errors; abjure reason.

   3. To recant or retract.

   4. To banish. [Not used.]
